  "footnotes": [
    "Western Anatolia: Ionian Greek city-states (Miletus, Ephesus, Smyrna) pioneered early philosophy and science; Pergamon's library and Attalid art rivalled Alexandria",
    "Central Anatolia: Göbekli Tepe (c.9500 BCE) is among the world's oldest monumental architecture; Çatalhöyük was a proto-urban Neolithic settlement (c.7500–5700 BCE)",
    "The 1st Anatolian Beyliks arose after the Seljuk victory at Manzikert (1071); the 2nd Beyliks emerged after the Mongol victory at Köse Dağ (1243) fragmented the Rum Sultanate",
    "The Ankara Battle (1402): Timur defeated Sultan Bayezid I, temporarily restoring the beyliks during the Ottoman Interregnum (1402–1413) before Ottoman reunification under Mehmed I",
    "The Treaty of Sèvres (1920) proposed partitioning Anatolia among Greece, Armenia, France, Italy, and a Kurdish state; the Turkish War of Independence annulled it, establishing the Republic of Turkey in 1923"
  ]
